{"lemma":"سَماعِ","slug":"سَماعِ","root":"س.م.ع","root_slug":"س-م-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَماعِ","root":"سمع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20724","n20725","n20731"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَمِعَ (samiʕa, “hearing”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"attestation (perceived as a form of hearing or receiving)","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"(with ال (al-, “the”)) the act of listening to music","tags":["archaic","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"(with ال (al-, “the”)) the act of listening to music; (with ال (al-, “the”)) music","tags":["archaic","uncountable"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"receptive, acceptive, or absorptive (of ideas, information, and so on); attentive","examples":[{"text":"سَمَّاعُونَ لِلْكَذِبِ أَكَّالُونَ لِلسُّحْتِ ۚ فَإِن جَاؤُوكَ فَٱحْكُم بَيْنَهُم أَوْ أَعْرِضْ عَنْهُمْ ۖ وَإِن تُعْرِضْ عَنْهُمْ فَلَن يَضُرُّوكَ شَيْئًا ۖ وَإِنْ حَكَمْتَ فَٱحْكُم بَيْنَهُمْ بِٱلْقِسْطِ ۚ إِنَّ ٱللَّهَ يُحِبُّ الْمُقْسِطِينَ","english":"Absorbers of lies, eaters of [shameful and worthless] trash! If they [ever] come to you, either judge their quarrels and disputes or turn away from them. If you [do] turn away, they cannot [ever] harm you, but if you judge, then judge fairly. Allah likes the fair."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"hear!, listen!, hark!","tags":["defective"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20724","headword_ar":"سَمَاعٍ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an imperative verbal n.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hear thou:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraAki","text_ar":"دَرَاكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAEi","text_ar":"مَنَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoriko","text_ar":"اَدْرِكْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimonaEo","text_ar":"اِمْنَعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20725","headword_ar":"سَمَاعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see its syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; first sentence. ―         -b2-  Also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isomaAEN","text_ar":"اـِسْمَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in three exs. expl. above; see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the middle portion of the paragraph. ―         -b3-  Also [an inf. n. used in the sense of a pass. part. n., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What has been heard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heard of:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that one has heard of, and that has become current, and talked of."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence, used in lexicology and grammar as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What has been received by hearsay;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is established by received usage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoSuwrN EalaY Als~amaAEi","text_ar":"مَقْصُورٌ عَلَى السَّمَاعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restricted to what has been received by hearsay;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA*~N","text_ar":"شَاذٌّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Als~amaAEi","text_ar":"فِى السَّمَاعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deviating from the constant course of speech with respect to what has been receeived by hearsay;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; which virtually means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deviating from what is established by received usage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ what has been received by hearsay ” always meaning “ what has been heard, either immediately or mediately, from one or more of the Arabs of the classical times. ”] ―         -b4-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is heard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being heard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of discourse, or narration, and of matters of science. See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muri*~N","text_ar":"مُرِذٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r*","text_ar":"رذ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-  And [hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Singing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"song;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"musical performance whether vocal"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"instrumental"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"both combined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant sound in which the ears take delight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAta fiY lahowK wasamaAEK","text_ar":"بَاتَ فِى لَهْوٍ وَسَمَاعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed the night in"},{"kind":"text","text":"the enjoyment of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diversion and singing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) [See an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$aArN","text_ar":"مُشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wr","text_ar":"شور"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoEN","text_ar":"سِمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20731","headword_ar":"سَمَّاعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who hearkens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"listens, much to what is said, and utters it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Its primary signification is simply One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who hears, hearkens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"listens, much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habitually:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick of hearing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmiEN","text_ar":"سَامِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spy, who searches for information, and brings it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Obedient."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}